Updated bundled Swift templates for Swift 2.

Finally™
Don't try to generic-ize Swift Sets.
Removed the // validate comments out of the machine generated templates since they don't do anything.
Nullability attributes for Objective-C machine templates
prefer instancetype instead of id where appropriate in the machine generated ObjC headers
Switch out structs with __unsafe_unretained NSString * objects for attribute/relationship/etc keys in favor of full on NSObject subclasses. ARC, baby!

More explicit TargetConditional intentions

First we check to see if we are on the iOS or tvOS. If not, then we defer back to OS X.

TARGET_OS_IPHONE is a variant of TARGET_OS_MAC, which makes this whole thing really stupid.
